Queen's Doughnuts is a family owned business that has been a regular stop of the driver's of the highly travelled Durfee Avenue as well as the local residents in southern El Monte. This shop features everything from your typical doughnut selection, hot sandwiches to an extensive array of boba drinks and also "Thrifty" brand Ice Cream for a cold treat. There are a number of other cold bottled beverages available as well as snacks like potato chips to boot.<//review>

< text>
If I could give these guys 10 stars, I would.  I was on a long-distance drive from Northern California to Ohio via "the southern route" (I-10 & I-40) and had spent the night in Indio.  On the road east-bound at 7 AM and 10 miles east of Indio my dreaded "check engine" light came on.  I quickly checked and no fluids or smells, so I turned around and went back to Indio.  USAA Roadside Assistance referred me to Encore and my Suburban was diagnosed with bad oxygen sensor.  Diagnosis and repair took less than 90 minutes. They literally saved the day for me.  Fantastic service and Holman from Encore texted me two days later to make sure all was good with the Suburban.  You just can't get customer service like this anymore and when you do, you support the business and the people!<//text>

< Text>
I had a really bad experience at this ER a Friday night. I went there according to my health insurance after my finger was wounded. After an X-Ray, the diagnosis was a broken bone and laceration. After cleaning the wound, the doctor put 4 staples on my pinky, gave me antibiotics for 7days and told to have the staples removed in 7days. As I was worry about seeing the flesh out the injury, I showed my regular doctor my finger and he urged me to meet a hand specialist doctor. I did and the specialist said they did a really bad job because it's totally abnormal to put staples on this severe laceration! ER also never told me to keep my hand raised and immobilized. Because of that, my finger was still swollen and the specialist couldn't remove the staples, so I lost at least one week of healing. I'm still worried of my next visit to the specialist and I hope I wouldn't have bad consequences following the bad job done by the ER. DON'T GO THERE, please!< /Text>

<date>1460337442338<//date><rate>5< /rate><text>We originally went to Harborside but the line was so long and the place so crowded that we chose Pan Bon, and I'm SO GLAD WE DID! It's been over a yet since our first visit. Things were a little off then. What a difference! The service was outstanding and friendly and prompt. The cappuccino made just the way I like it with perfect ratio of half and half. I ordered the Pan Bon Breakfast. Eggs made three ways, Over easy, poached and scrambled. We had nice conversation with our server and were made to feel at home. All the water you can drink at your own pace. This was by far one of the most welcoming and most delightful places I have ever been too. The servers are all smiling and joyful ready to get you anything and recommend the greatest food. And the food! My word I think I ate one of every pastry and dessert they have because it was all phenonenal! I had to come back the next morning for breakfast just to try more! The breads are all so fresh, even the pasta is homemade daily! This restaurant is still fairly new and up and coming but it is by far the best meal I have had in all of little Italy! I wish them all the best of luck and hope they are quite successful.< /review>

<user_name>John Thomas< /user_name><time>1460954737815< /time><Rate>4< /Rate>< Review>
This cozy little Italian restaurant was by far the best Italian food I have ever had in SD. I have traveled worldwide and I absolutely adore the authentic food in Italy more than anything. Everything was perfect and just as good as my experiences in the Mediterranean. Many compliments to the chef especially for the fish and the pasta and of course my favorite being the wine. <userid>110604278924779557659< /userid><user_name>Giacomo Pizzigoni< /user_name>< time>
1423873895591</time>
<rate>5< /rate>< Text>
I've been in San Diego for more than 4 years and I can tell you that this is one of the best Italian meals I've had since I came down here from Milano, my hometown.
It really feels like I'm back in Italy, the owners are from Verona, Romeo and Juliet town, and they brought the flavors and traditions of their land to San Diego.
The atmosphere is cozy and warm, the food is superb and everyone working here is very nice and attentive.
They have a restaurant where they serve lunch and dinner, as well as a bakery and pastry shop where you can buy a cappuccino and a croissant and enjoy it sitting down at the table.
And they make their own bead which is superb!
On my first visit I tried the gnocchi di Malga, homemade ricotta dumplings with creamy Gorgonzola sauce, are among the best gnocchi I have ever had, the flavor is unique and they melt in your mouth.
If you live in SD or happen to stop by for few days, you MUST try Pan Bon</Text>

< Text>
Reading reviews online and believing them has bitten me more than once.

The short review: The pizza is decent

The long review:  I walked in to order.  The man must have been having a bad day, he didn't look like he wanted to be there.  Who would...it is 100 degrees outside and they have no air conditioning inside...what's up with that?

I place my order and tell him that I really like mushrooms and asked if I should order extra mushrooms to make sure i get my fill of them...he said "no, we put plenty on, you'll like it.  If you don't, order more next time".  I said Okay and paid for the pizza.

As I walked over to sit down to wait for the pizza (sweating) a cockroach crawls across the floor, in broad daylight!  I've seen some roaches in my time, and they don't like to come out in the day time unless they are very comfortable doing so.   Given the location of the restaurant, roaches do not seem out of place.

The rest of the place seemed clean, but when I got my pizza, it smelled good and i took it to the hotel.  When I opened the box, I was a bit disappointed in the number of mushrooms...should have ordered extra :(

For what it's worth, I won't get pizza there again while I'm going to be here in the area.  It was better than the cheap joints, not the best I've had though.</Text>

< review>
I was in an accident on 05/19/14 ‚Äì I drove home from work and as traffic started to slow down, a truck drove into me, pushing me into the vehicle in front. The driver admitted later to have been driving at 60 mph. I was brought to the hospital and diagnosed with ‚Äì only - severe whiplash.

After approx. four weeks I was contacted by the opponent‚Äôs insurance company in regards to a settlement. I inquired from the agent what that entails. He did not give me any satisfactory answers, so I called my own agent. Same thing here ‚Ä¶ ooh, just send in your hospital bill, ambulance bill, etc.

I was upset and discussed this issue with a co-worker, who suggested I should get legal advice. Well, I went on the internet and chose the services of Michael Pine.

I called and explained what happened. Mr. Pines asked me whether I was in the same shape as before my accident ‚Äì this I had to deny. My back was still hurting and he stated that, if I would accept his services, he would ensure that I would get the therapy I needed (up to this point I was treated with pain killers). He also ensured me that all bills would be paid and my health restored.

Michael Pines and his team have kept this promise. During this ordeal I called the office on various occasions to get an update. His upbeat staff was able to answer all questions in a timely manner.

I can recommend the services of this law office and would not hesitate to request them again if I would have need of them.< /review>

< review>
I've always had a soft spot for trampolines but the older I get the less able I am to enjoy this sport for more than 10 minutes. Today is until I went to Sky Zone and played trampolines dodge ball. I suddenly got a second wind and jumped around for another 30 minutes as time stopped as I tried to physically destroy my opponents. More fun, or sweat, can not be had on under an hour for so cheap. You need to get here. Now.</review>

< Review>
I made the grave error of going to Sky Zone Covina. When you go, they make you sign a waiver, and they email you a copy. And then they put you on the email marketing list. And then they spam you.
You may click on the unsubscribe button, which I did on seven separate occasions.
You may call them and talk to them asking them to stop, which I did on three separate occasions.
You may explain to them on Facebook and Twitter and on Sky Zone's corporate page that spam is ILLEGAL and please for the love of god make it stop.
But they will keep. spamming. you.
There is no end to it.
Do you want to receive emails for the rest of your natural life about GLOW NIGHT and how they're DIFFERENT AFTER DARK?

<user>100313420030963183375</user>< gmapID>

< Rate>
3<//Rate>
<Name>Ruben Moreno<//Name>< Date>
1471796654944</Date>
</record></dataset><record>
<pics>None<//pics>< Review>
If you want to let out your inner child, there's no better way then visiting Sky Zone indoor trampoline park!

I've heard so much about Sky Zone from friends and was thrilled when I saw that a Sky Zone was opening a couple miles way. This past weekend a group of my friends decided to take advantage of the $20 Saturday night deal for unlimited access from 9pm-12am (socks included, they usually charge $2 during regular hours).

The line was incredibly long when we arrived and to save time I highly suggest filling out the waiver beforehand. We waited about 20 minutes before we were able to pay admission and get our socks. Since we came during their Saturday night special, the place was extremely crowded and there were a bunch of kids everywhere. I definitely think I would have had a better experience if I came during off hours and were surrounded by people my own age.

Apparently the Covina Sky Zone is also smaller than some of the other locations. They have a dodgeball court, basketball area, foam pit, a general jumping area, and another area they closed off for private parties. When it got crowded, there were lines for everything and it took away from precious jumping time. I heard from my friends that the Anaheim location has two dodgeball courts so it could accommodate more people.

Overall I had an awesome time with my friends. Everyone should try Sky Zone at least once.  I also never thought jumping on trampolines could be so tiring. I definitely ran out of breath a couple times and had to rest quite a bit.

Tip* Leave valuables in your car. Lockers are available for 50 cents and there's a shoe rack  for you to place your belongings.< /Review>
